caption.text:
There was once a love story between a prince, running away and hiding from his palace, and a lady from a little village nearby the kingdom's water supply.

As a proof of his love for this tough girl, he planted a banana tree on a rock in the stream, that soon grew to be an orchard full of banana trees. In his words were stated that if their love was approved by the almighty, the trees would be his legacy that would bring wealth for their descendants of seven generation, and no one else can ever harvest from it.

One day, his grandson, told by his mother, looked for the orchard, found it and harvested three sprouts from it to be re-planted on his yard and his children's.

One year later, the rest of the trees are gone and no one knows who, when, how, and why.

SMA Kanisius Jakarta is representing the Republic of Indonesia in the World School International Forum 2015 in Italy, addressing the theme of "Feeding the Planet: Energy for Life". Three students and one teacher will be sent as delegates of Indonesia, bringing our diverse culture into a global forum to be shared and to appreciate the difference of other cultures over the world, while together standing as one trying to compete all problems happening across the globe nowadays in the spirit of unity.

Wishes of good luck and success!
